<translate>
=== Using email links === <!--T:157-->
</translate>
<translate><!--T:216--> Email links use <tvar name=1><code>mailto:</code></tvar> before the address.</translate>
<translate><!--T:219--> They're written like this: {{<tvar name=1>tmpl|0=<code><nowiki>[mailto:anyone@example.org</nowiki> $1<nowiki>]</nowiki></code></tvar>|address name}} (resulting in {{<tvar name=2>tmpl|0=[mailto:anyone@example.org $1]</tvar>|address name}}).</translate>
<translate><!--T:217--> If there's no name, the address is automatically numbered, like this: <tvar name=1><code><nowiki>[mailto:anyone@example.org]</nowiki></code></tvar> becomes <tvar name=2>[mailto:anyone@example.org]</tvar>.</translate>

<translate>
<!--T:218-->
Addresses without square brackets won't be linked, e.g., <tvar name=1>anyone@example.com</tvar>.

<!--T:220-->
You can also add a CC using {{<tvar name=1>tmpl|0=<code><nowiki>[mailto:anyone@example.org?cc=anyone2@example.org</nowiki> $1<nowiki>]</nowiki></code></tvar>|address name}} (resulting in {{<tvar name=2>tmpl|0=[mailto:anyone@example.org?cc=anyone2@example.org $1]</tvar>|address name}}).
</translate>

<translate><!--T:243--> To add a subject, use:</translate>
<code><nowiki>[mailto:anyone@example.com?subject=</nowiki>Subject<nowiki>]</nowiki></code>

